        "text": "A fair coin is flipped 10 times. What is the probability of getting exactly 6 heads?",
        "answers": [
            {
                "is_correct": true,
                "text": "0.2051",
                "reason": "Correct. The probability is calculated using the binomial formula: $P(X=6) = C(10,6) \\times (0.5)^{6} \\times (0.5)^{4} = 210 \\times (0.5)^{10} \\approx 0.2051$."
            },
            {
                "is_correct": false,
                "text": "0.1172",
                "reason": "Incorrect. This is the probability of getting exactly 3 heads."
            },
            {
